race.comment: Tough way to finish. BELLEZZE (5) is a lightly raced mare with a bit of upside. Easy maiden winner two back then a solid fourth latest in tougher company. Drawn for a soft run and should be hard to hold out with even luck. MEG'S MAGIC (18) is fitter for two runs back and looks ready to fire. Well placed this company and drawn for a good run with cover. STARTIDE (9) is in great form with a win two back then a placing last time. Rates strongly on best but will need a little luck from the horror draw but does have a form jockey aboard. OMAHA DAWN (6) followed a second at Murray Bridge two runs ago with a win last start over 1200m at Balaklava, finishing a neck ahead of her rivals. Must be considered.
